    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'What kind of gifts do you prefer?'"
        },
        "text": "To be more specific about gifts, you can ask 'أي نوع من الهدايا تُفَضِّلُ؟' (Which type of gifts do you prefer?). 'نوع' means 'type' or 'kind'. 'تُفَضِّلُ' is the verb 'to prefer'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أي نوع من الهدايا تُفَضِّلُ؟",
            "english": "What kind of gifts do you (male) prefer?",
            "transliteration": "Ayy naw' min al-hadāyā tufaddilu?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'تُ' and 'لُ' distinguish male singular present tense from the feminine form."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أي نوع من الهدايا تُفَضِّلِينَ؟",
            "english": "What kind of gifts do you (female) prefer?",
            "transliteration": "Ayy naw' min al-hadāyā tufaddilīna?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'ينَ' ending indicates feminine singular present tense."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "أي نوع من الهدايا تُفَضِّلُ؟ أي نوع من الهدايا تُفَضِّلِينَ؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing 'I like X gifts.'"
        },
        "text": "You can describe the type of gifts you like by adding an adjective after 'الهدايا الـ...'. For example, 'practical' is 'عملية' (amaliyya) and 'simple' is 'بسيطة' (basīṭa). Remember that adjectives follow the noun in gender and number.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أُحِبُّ الهدايا العملية.",
            "english": "I like practical gifts.",
            "transliteration": "Uḥibbu al-hadāyā al-'amaliyya.",
            "diacriticalNotes": "Adjective 'عملية' agrees with plural feminine 'الهدايا'."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أُفَضِّلُ الهدايا البسيطة.",
            "english": "I prefer simple gifts.",
            "transliteration": "Ufaḍḍilu al-hadāyā al-basīṭa.",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The 'أُفَضِّلُ' form is for 'I prefer'."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "أُحِبُّ الهدايا العملية. أُفَضِّلُ الهدايا البسيطة."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing 'I don't like Y gifts.'"
        },
        "text": "To express a dislike, you simply add 'لا' (lā) before the verb 'أُحِبُّ' (uḥibbu) or 'أُفَضِّلُ' (ufaḍḍilu). For instance, 'expensive' is 'غالية' (ghāliya) and 'complicated' is 'معقدة' (mu'aqqada).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لا أُحِبُّ الهدايا الغالية.",
            "english": "I don't like expensive gifts.",
            "transliteration": "Lā uḥibbu al-hadāyā al-ghāliya.",
            "diacriticalNotes": "'لا' for negation."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لا أُفَضِّلُ الهدايا المعقدة.",
            "english": "I don't prefer complicated gifts.",
            "transliteration": "Lā ufaḍḍilu al-hadāyā al-mu'aqqada.",
            "diacriticalNotes": "'لا' for negation."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "لا أُحِبُّ الهدايا الغالية. لا أُفَضِّلُ الهدايا المعقدة."
